3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* post_mail 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* convenient mail posting interface
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <post_mail.h>
10/*
11/* VSTREAM *post_mail_fopen(sender, recipient, source_class, trace_flags,
12/* utf8_flags, queue_id)
13/* const char *sender;
14/* const char *recipient;
15/* int source_class;
16/* int trace_flags;
17/* int utf8_flags;
18/* VSTRING *queue_id;
19/*
20/* VSTREAM *post_mail_fopen_nowait(sender, recipient, source_class,
21/* trace_flags, utf8_flags, queue_id)
22/* const char *sender;
23/* const char *recipient;
24/* int source_class;
25/* int trace_flags;
26/* int utf8_flags;
27/* VSTRING *queue_id;
28/*
29/* void post_mail_fopen_async(sender, recipient, source_class,
30/* trace_flags, utf8_flags,
31/* queue_id, notify, context)
32/* const char *sender;
33/* const char *recipient;
34/* int source_class;
35/* int trace_flags;
36/* int utf8_flags;
37/* VSTRING *queue_id;
38/* void (*notify)(VSTREAM *stream, void *context);
39/* void *context;
40/*
41/* int post_mail_fprintf(stream, format, ...)
42/* VSTREAM *stream;
43/* const char *format;
44/*
45/* int post_mail_fputs(stream, str)
46/* VSTREAM *stream;
47/* const char *str;
48/*
49/* int post_mail_buffer(stream, buf, len)
50/* VSTREAM *stream;
51/* const char *buffer;
52/*
53/* int POST_MAIL_BUFFER(stream, buf)
54/* VSTREAM *stream;
55/* VSTRING *buffer;
56/*
57/* int post_mail_fclose(stream)
58/* VSTREAM *STREAM;
59/*
60/* void post_mail_fclose_async(stream, notify, context)
61/* VSTREAM *stream;
62/* void (*notify)(int status, void *context);
63/* void *context;
64/* DESCRIPTION
65/* This module provides a convenient interface for the most
66/* common case of sending one message to one recipient. It
67/* allows the application to concentrate on message content,
68/* without having to worry about queue file structure details.
69/*
70/* post_mail_fopen() opens a connection to the cleanup service
71/* and waits until the service is available, does some option
72/* negotiation, generates message envelope records, and generates
73/* Received: and Date: message headers. The result is a stream
74/* handle that can be used for sending message records.
75/*
76/* post_mail_fopen_nowait() tries to contact the cleanup service
77/* only once, and does not wait until the cleanup service is
78/* available. Otherwise it is identical to post_mail_fopen().
79/*
80/* post_mail_fopen_async() contacts the cleanup service and
81/* invokes the caller-specified notify routine, with the
82/* open stream and the caller-specified context when the
83/* service responds, or with a null stream and the caller-specified
84/* context when the request could not be completed. It is the
85/* responsability of the application to close an open stream.
86/*
87/* post_mail_fprintf() formats message content (header or body)
88/* and sends it to the cleanup service.
89/*
90/* post_mail_fputs() sends pre-formatted content (header or body)
91/* to the cleanup service.
92/*
93/* post_mail_buffer() sends a pre-formatted buffer to the
94/* cleanup service.
95/*
96/* POST_MAIL_BUFFER() is a wrapper for post_mail_buffer() that
97/* evaluates its buffer argument more than once.
98/*
99/* post_mail_fclose() completes the posting of a message.
100/*
101/* post_mail_fclose_async() completes the posting of a message
102/* and upon completion invokes the caller-specified notify
103/* routine, with the cleanup status and caller-specified context
104/* as arguments.
105/*
106/* Arguments:
107/* .IP sender
108/* The sender envelope address. It is up to the application
109/* to produce From: headers.
110/* .IP recipient
111/* The recipient envelope address. It is up to the application
112/* to produce To: headers.
113/* .IP source_class
114/* The message source class, as defined in \fB<mail_proto.h>\fR.
115/* Depending on the setting of the internal_mail_source_classes
116/* and smtputf8_autodetect_classes parameters, the message
117/* will or won't be subject to content inspection or SMTPUTF8
118/* autodetection.
119/* .IP trace_flags
120/* Message tracing flags as specified in \fB<deliver_request.h>\fR.
121/* .IP utf8_flags
122/* Flags defined in <smtputf8.h>. Flags other than
123/* SMTPUTF8_FLAG_REQUESTED are ignored.
124/* .IP queue_id
125/* Null pointer, or pointer to buffer that receives the queue
126/* ID of the new message.
127/* .IP stream
128/* A stream opened by mail_post_fopen().
129/* .IP notify
130/* Application call-back routine.
131/* .IP context
132/* Application call-back context.
133/* DIAGNOSTICS
134/* post_mail_fopen_nowait() returns a null pointer when the
135/* cleanup service is not available immediately.
136/*
137/* post_mail_fopen_async() returns a null pointer when the
138/* attempt to contact the cleanup service fails immediately.
139/*
140/* post_mail_fprintf(), post_mail_fputs() post_mail_fclose(),
141/* and post_mail_buffer() return the binary OR of the error
142/* status codes defined in \fI<cleanup_user.h>\fR.
143/*
144/* Fatal errors: cleanup initial handshake errors. This means
145/* the client and server speak incompatible protocols.
146/* SEE ALSO
147/* cleanup_user(3h) cleanup options and results
148/* cleanup_strerror(3) translate results to text
149/* cleanup(8) cleanup service
150/* LICENSE
151/* .ad
152/* .fi
153/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
154/* AUTHOR(S)
155/* Wietse Venema
156/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
157/* P.O. Box 704
158/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
159/*--*/
160

187 /*
188 * Call-back state for asynchronous connection requests.
189 */
190typedef struct {
191 char *sender;
192 char *recipient;
193 int source_class;
194 int trace_flags;
195 int utf8_flags;
196 POST_MAIL_NOTIFY notify;
197 void *context;
198 VSTREAM *stream;
199 VSTRING *queue_id;
200} POST_MAIL_STATE;
201
202 /*
203 * Call-back state for asynchronous close requests.
204 */
205typedef struct {
206 int status;
207 VSTREAM *stream;
208 POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_NOTIFY notify;
209 void *context;
210} POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_STATE;
211
212/* post_mail_init - initial negotiations */
213
214static void post_mail_init(VSTREAM *stream, const char *sender,
215 const char *recipient,
216 int source_class, int trace_flags,
217 int utf8_flags, VSTRING *queue_id)
218{
219 VSTRING *id = queue_id ? queue_id : vstring_alloc(100);
220 struct timeval now;
221 const char *date;
222 int cleanup_flags =
223 int_filt_flags(source_class) | CLEANUP_FLAG_MASK_INTERNAL
224 | smtputf8_autodetect(source_class)
225 | ((utf8_flags & SMTPUTF8_FLAG_REQUESTED) ? CLEANUP_FLAG_SMTPUTF8 : 0);
226
227 GETTIMEOFDAY(&now);
228 date = mail_date(now.tv_sec);
229
230 /*
231 * XXX Don't flush buffers while sending the initial message records.
232 * That would cause deadlock between verify(8) and cleanup(8) servers.
233 */
234 vstream_control(stream, VSTREAM_CTL_BUFSIZE, 2 * VSTREAM_BUFSIZE,
235 VSTREAM_CTL_END);
236
237 /*
238 * Negotiate with the cleanup service. Give up if we can't agree.
239 */
240 if (attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
241 RECV_ATTR_STR(MAIL_ATTR_QUEUEID, id),
242 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1
243 || attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
244 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_FLAGS, cleanup_flags),
245 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 0)
246 msg_fatal("unable to contact the %s service", var_cleanup_service);
247
248 /*
249 * Generate a minimal envelope section. The cleanup service will add a
250 * size record.
251 */
252 rec_fprintf(stream, REC_TYPE_TIME, REC_TYPE_TIME_FORMAT,
253 REC_TYPE_TIME_ARG(now));
254 rec_fprintf(stream, REC_TYPE_ATTR, "%s=%s",
255 MAIL_ATTR_LOG_ORIGIN, MAIL_ATTR_ORG_LOCAL);
256 rec_fprintf(stream, REC_TYPE_ATTR, "%s=%d",
257 MAIL_ATTR_TRACE_FLAGS, trace_flags);
258 rec_fputs(stream, REC_TYPE_FROM, sender);
259 rec_fputs(stream, REC_TYPE_RCPT, recipient);
260 rec_fputs(stream, REC_TYPE_MESG, "");
261
262 /*
263 * Do the Received: and Date: header lines. This allows us to shave a few
264 * cycles by using the expensive date conversion result for both.
265 */
266 post_mail_fprintf(stream, "Received: by %s (%s)",
267 var_myhostname, var_mail_name);
268 post_mail_fprintf(stream, "\tid %s; %s", vstring_str(id), date);
269 post_mail_fprintf(stream, "Date: %s", date);
270 if (queue_id == 0)
271 vstring_free(id);
272}
273
274/* post_mail_fopen - prepare for posting a message */
275
276VSTREAM *post_mail_fopen(const char *sender, const char *recipient,
277 int source_class, int trace_flags,
278 int utf8_flags, VSTRING *queue_id)
279{
280 VSTREAM *stream;
281
282 stream = mail_connect_wait(MAIL_CLASS_PUBLIC, var_cleanup_service);
283 post_mail_init(stream, sender, recipient, source_class, trace_flags,
284 utf8_flags, queue_id);
285 return (stream);
286}
287
288/* post_mail_fopen_nowait - prepare for posting a message */
289
290VSTREAM *post_mail_fopen_nowait(const char *sender, const char *recipient,
291 int source_class, int trace_flags,
292 int utf8_flags, VSTRING *queue_id)
293{
294 VSTREAM *stream;
295
296 if ((stream = mail_connect(MAIL_CLASS_PUBLIC, var_cleanup_service,
297 BLOCKING)) != 0)
298 post_mail_init(stream, sender, recipient, source_class, trace_flags,
299 utf8_flags, queue_id);
300 else
301 msg_warn("connect to %s/%s: %m",
302 MAIL_CLASS_PUBLIC, var_cleanup_service);
303 return (stream);
304}
305
306/* post_mail_open_event - handle asynchronous connection events */
307
308static void post_mail_open_event(int event, void *context)
309{
310 POST_MAIL_STATE *state = (POST_MAIL_STATE *) context;
311 const char *myname = "post_mail_open_event";
312
313 switch (event) {
314
315 /*
316 * Initial server reply. Stop the watchdog timer, disable further
317 * read events that end up calling this function, and notify the
318 * requestor.
319 */
320 case EVENT_READ:
321 if (msg_verbose)
322 msg_info("%s: read event", myname);
323 event_cancel_timer(post_mail_open_event, context);
324 event_disable_readwrite(vstream_fileno(state->stream));
325 non_blocking(vstream_fileno(state->stream), BLOCKING);
326 post_mail_init(state->stream, state->sender,
327 state->recipient, state->source_class,
328 state->trace_flags, state->utf8_flags,
329 state->queue_id);
330 myfree(state->sender);
331 myfree(state->recipient);
332 state->notify(state->stream, state->context);
333 myfree((void *) state);
334 return;
335
336 /*
337 * No connection or no initial reply within a conservative time
338 * limit. The system is broken and we give up.
339 */
340 case EVENT_TIME:
341 if (state->stream) {
342 msg_warn("timeout connecting to service: %s", var_cleanup_service);
343 event_disable_readwrite(vstream_fileno(state->stream));
344 vstream_fclose(state->stream);
345 } else {
346 msg_warn("connect to service: %s: %m", var_cleanup_service);
347 }
348 myfree(state->sender);
349 myfree(state->recipient);
350 state->notify((VSTREAM *) 0, state->context);
351 myfree((void *) state);
352 return;
353
354 /*
355 * Some exception.
356 */
357 case EVENT_XCPT:
358 msg_warn("error connecting to service: %s", var_cleanup_service);
359 event_cancel_timer(post_mail_open_event, context);
360 event_disable_readwrite(vstream_fileno(state->stream));
361 vstream_fclose(state->stream);
362 myfree(state->sender);
363 myfree(state->recipient);
364 state->notify((VSTREAM *) 0, state->context);
365 myfree((void *) state);
366 return;
367
368 /*
369 * Broken software or hardware.
370 */
371 default:
372 msg_panic("%s: unknown event type %d", myname, event);
373 }
374}
375
376/* post_mail_fopen_async - prepare for posting a message */
377
378void post_mail_fopen_async(const char *sender, const char *recipient,
379 int source_class, int trace_flags,
380 int utf8_flags, VSTRING *queue_id,
381 void (*notify) (VSTREAM *, void *),
382 void *context)
383{
384 VSTREAM *stream;
385 POST_MAIL_STATE *state;
386
387 stream = mail_connect(MAIL_CLASS_PUBLIC, var_cleanup_service, NON_BLOCKING);
388 state = (POST_MAIL_STATE *) mymalloc(sizeof(*state));
389 state->sender = mystrdup(sender);
390 state->recipient = mystrdup(recipient);
391 state->source_class = source_class;
392 state->trace_flags = trace_flags;
393 state->utf8_flags = utf8_flags;
394 state->notify = notify;
395 state->context = context;
396 state->stream = stream;
397 state->queue_id = queue_id;
398
399 /*
400 * To keep interfaces as simple as possible we report all errors via the
401 * same interface as all successes.
402 */
403 if (stream != 0) {
404 event_enable_read(vstream_fileno(stream), post_mail_open_event,
405 (void *) state);
406 event_request_timer(post_mail_open_event, (void *) state,
407 var_daemon_timeout);
408 } else {
409 event_request_timer(post_mail_open_event, (void *) state, 0);
410 }
411}
412
413/* post_mail_fprintf - format and send message content */
414
415int post_mail_fprintf(VSTREAM *cleanup, const char *format,...)
416{
417 int status;
418 va_list ap;
419
420 va_start(ap, format);
421 status = rec_vfprintf(cleanup, REC_TYPE_NORM, format, ap);
422 va_end(ap);
423 return (status != REC_TYPE_NORM ? CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE : 0);
424}
425
426/* post_mail_buffer - send pre-formatted buffer */
427
428int post_mail_buffer(VSTREAM *cleanup, const char *buf, int len)
429{
430 return (rec_put(cleanup, REC_TYPE_NORM, buf, len) != REC_TYPE_NORM ?
431 CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE : 0);
432}
433
434/* post_mail_fputs - send pre-formatted message content */
435
436int post_mail_fputs(VSTREAM *cleanup, const char *str)
437{
438 ssize_t len = str ? strlen(str) : 0;
439
440 return (rec_put(cleanup, REC_TYPE_NORM, str, len) != REC_TYPE_NORM ?
441 CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE : 0);
442}
443
444/* post_mail_fclose - finish posting of message */
445
446int post_mail_fclose(VSTREAM *cleanup)
447{
448 int status = 0;
449
450 /*
451 * Send the message end marker only when there were no errors.
452 */
453 if (vstream_ferror(cleanup) != 0) {
454 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
455 } else {
456 rec_fputs(cleanup, REC_TYPE_XTRA, "");
457 rec_fputs(cleanup, REC_TYPE_END, "");
458 if (vstream_fflush(cleanup)
459 || attr_scan(cleanup, ATTR_FLAG_MISSING,
460 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
461 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1)
462 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
463 }
464 (void) vstream_fclose(cleanup);
465 return (status);
466}
467
468/* post_mail_fclose_event - event handler */
469
470static void post_mail_fclose_event(int event, void *context)
471{
472 POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_STATE *state = (POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_STATE *) context;
473 int status = state->status;
474
475 switch (event) {
476
477 /*
478 * Final server reply. Pick up the completion status.
479 */
480 case EVENT_READ:
481 if (status == 0) {
482 if (vstream_ferror(state->stream) != 0
483 || attr_scan(state->stream, ATTR_FLAG_MISSING,
484 ATTR_TYPE_INT, MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status,
485 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1)
486 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
487 }
488 break;
489
490 /*
491 * No response or error.
492 */
493 default:
494 msg_warn("error talking to service: %s", var_cleanup_service);
495 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
496 break;
497 }
498
499 /*
500 * Stop the watchdog timer, and disable further read events that end up
501 * calling this function.
502 */
503 event_cancel_timer(post_mail_fclose_event, context);
504 event_disable_readwrite(vstream_fileno(state->stream));
505
506 /*
507 * Notify the requestor and clean up.
508 */
509 state->notify(status, state->context);
510 (void) vstream_fclose(state->stream);
511 myfree((void *) state);
512}
513
514/* post_mail_fclose_async - finish posting of message */
515
516void post_mail_fclose_async(VSTREAM *stream,
517 void (*notify) (int status, void *context),
518 void *context)
519{
520 POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_STATE *state;
521 int status = 0;
522
523
524 /*
525 * Send the message end marker only when there were no errors.
526 */
527 if (vstream_ferror(stream) != 0) {
528 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
529 } else {
530 rec_fputs(stream, REC_TYPE_XTRA, "");
531 rec_fputs(stream, REC_TYPE_END, "");
532 if (vstream_fflush(stream))
533 status = CLEANUP_STAT_WRITE;
534 }
535
536 /*
537 * Bundle up the suspended state.
538 */
539 state = (POST_MAIL_FCLOSE_STATE *) mymalloc(sizeof(*state));
540 state->status = status;
541 state->stream = stream;
542 state->notify = notify;
543 state->context = context;
544
545 /*
546 * To keep interfaces as simple as possible we report all errors via the
547 * same interface as all successes.
548 */
549 if (status == 0) {
550 event_enable_read(vstream_fileno(stream), post_mail_fclose_event,
551 (void *) state);
552 event_request_timer(post_mail_fclose_event, (void *) state,
553 var_daemon_timeout);
554 } else {
555 event_request_timer(post_mail_fclose_event, (void *) state, 0);
556 }
557}
